Ohanaeze Ndigbo youth wing has expressed solidarity with Ijaw youths in their call for restructuring of Nigeria. The body also expressed solidarity to Ijaw people on the just concluded activities to commemorate the 50th memorial of late icon, Isaac Jasper Boro. The Coordinator of Ohanaeze Youths Wing in South South zone, Chief Chinedu Arthur-Ugwa , while speaking with Daily Trust in Yenagoa yesterday, said that the group had enjoyed a harmonious relationship with Ijaw people in Niger Delta. He explained that Ohanaeze youths also participated in the week long activities, including processions, public lectures and exhibitions lined up for the 50th anniversary of Boroâ€™s demise.